He wanted to prove that he’s “someone,” he said, so he wouldn’t disappoint everyone when they finally learned about his sexuality.
The winner of two bronze medals at the Olympics became a renowned supporter of LGBT campaigns and took advantage of the appearance at this year’s Commonwealth Games in Australia to demand more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
